---
/**
 * context-engineering 0005 · Figure 2 — "Same query, two strategies": a
 * pre-indexed lookup versus a read-on-demand search resolving the same query.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the
 * footnote <sup>). Standalone .astro component (see Fig1 for the rationale).
 * Carries its own <defs> for the markers it references — #arw and #arwG.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 224"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A pre-indexed lookup versus a read-on-demand search resolving the same query."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="160" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Pre-indexed (embeddings)</text
        >
        <text x="480" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Read-on-demand (tools)</text
        >
        <!-- left -->
        <rect x="60" y="30" width="200" height="32" rx="6" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"
        ></rect><text
            x="160"
            y="50"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">query &rarr; embed</text
        >
        <rect x="60" y="80" width="200" height="32" rx="6" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"
        ></rect><text
            x="160"
            y="100"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#1f3a5a">vector lookup (1 hop)</text
        >
        <rect x="60" y="130" width="200" height="32" rx="6" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"
        ></rect><text
            x="160"
            y="150"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">top-k chunks</text
        >
        <line x1="160" y1="62" x2="160" y2="78" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="160" y1="112" x2="160" y2="128" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <text x="160" y="186" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
            >fast · but as stale as the index</text
        >
        <text x="160" y="202" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
            >&amp; blind to exact identifiers</text
        >
        <!-- right -->
        <rect x="380" y="30" width="200" height="32" rx="6" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text
            x="480"
            y="50"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">grep / glob</text
        >
        <rect x="380" y="80" width="200" height="32" rx="6" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text
            x="480"
            y="100"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#2f5d3a">read &rarr; follow imports</text
        >
        <rect x="380" y="130" width="200" height="32" rx="6" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text
            x="480"
            y="150"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">grep again (N hops)</text
        >
        <line x1="480" y1="62" x2="480" y2="78" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <line x1="480" y1="112" x2="480" y2="128" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <text x="480" y="186" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
            >fresh &amp; precise · but more</text
        >
        <text x="480" y="202" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
            >round-trips, and misses unsearched files</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        One hop versus N hops. Pre-index trades freshness for speed; read-on-demand trades speed for
        freshness and transparency. Neither is "better" — they fail differently, and the review
        names <em>which</em> failure your use-case can't tolerate.<sup
            ><a href="#s3" id="r3">3</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
